description: This operation invokes an API Gateway API asset. The request is proxied to the provider's API Gateway API.

parameters.name: QueryStringParameters
parameters.description: Attach query string parameters to the end of the URI (for example, /v1/examplePath?exampleParam=exampleValue). (string) --- (string) ---

parameters.name: AssetId
parameters.description: Asset ID value for the API request.

parameters.name: DataSetId
parameters.description: Data set ID value for the API request.

parameters.name: RequestHeaders
parameters.description: Any header value prefixed with x-amzn-dataexchange-header- will have that stripped before sending the Asset API request. Use this when you want to override a header that AWS Data Exchange uses. Alternatively, you can use the header without a prefix to the HTTP request. (string) --- (string) ---

parameters.name: RevisionId
parameters.description: Revision ID value for the API request.

nested_items.name: Body
nested_items.description: The response body from the underlying API tracked by the API asset.

nested_items.name: ResponseHeaders
nested_items.description: The response headers from the underlying API tracked by the API asset.
